Net (expense) revenue associated with medical care.
Information about revenues from public safety.
Program revenues used for health and welfare, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Information about emergency medical services receivable.
Allowance for accounts receivable, unbilled.
Revenue from State sources that the State Department of Education sends to district as a result of legislative statutory initiatives that are not grant programs. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Program revenues used for cemetery, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Information about revenue for other school district uses.
Cost incurred for lottery retailer commissions.
Revenue earned from miscellaneous court costs and fees.

Amounts paid for goods or services not properly classified in one of the objects included above Payments for refunds of prior year revenues are charged to this account. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue for non instructional services.

An Intergrant Transfer is when revenue is transferred from one grant to another, and those moneys are spent accordingly. Example: transfer Title II Part A "Teacher Quality" grant revenue (grant 4367) over to Title I (grant 4010), and spend the transferred Teacher Quality money as Title I money.
Amounts due from counties.
Amounts for specific revenues or gains that a local government unit defer to be recognized within the next reporting period.
Operating grants given to the local government unit to subsidize the entity's operation.
Revenue from federal sources that the State Department of Education sends to districts and Board of Cooperative Educational System.
Total capital contributions and transfers.

Costs incurred to support the operation of the cafeteria, bookstore, student organizations, athletics, and other related activities. It also includes all equipment, materials, supplies, and costs that are necessary to support this function.

Program revenues used for court equity which is a type of court that hears cases involving remedies other than monetary damages, such as injunctions, writs, or specific performance and a court of law, only hears cases involving monetary damages.

CARES Act relief fund amounts for which asset recognition criteria have been met (such as cash that has been received, or amounts that are receivable), but for which it has not met the revenue recognition requirements.
Net (expense) revenue associated with community risk management programs.
Revenues from a variety of sources for pupil activities. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Allowance for other accounts receivable.

This account is normally used in an Enterprise Fund to record the liability created when a customer is required to pay a deposit before receiving services. This is also used to record the liability for interest on customers’ deposits in those cases where an enterprise or utility has agreed to pay interest on such deposits.

Revenues from parks and recreation used on the General Fund or a Parks/Recreation Fund. It will reflect revenue earned by the parks or recreation department from other General Fund revenues. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amounts for emergency medical services receivable. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Name of other fund balance nonspendable which the reporting entity separately discloses in the same statement. Used with the disaggregation line item axis.
Program revenues used for community development block grants (CDBG).

Revenues for an appropriated reserve available for use by school district for emergencies caused by an act of God or arising from extraordinary problems or unforeseen emergencies and other unexpected events.
Information about net (expense) revenue for school districts.
Profit earned from arbitrage that must be paid back (or rebated) to the federal government
Tax, utility and assessment receivables.
Revenue earned from fines.
Amounts to be returned to persons or firms which overpaid taxes.
Net (expense) revenue court from attorney fee reimbursement charges.
Change cash.
Operating revenue from contributions and premiums.

Revenue earned from public safety services, generated by the police or sheriff department. Used in the General Fund or Police (Sheriff) Fund of local units of government that have such an activity. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amount of estimated obligation for costs related to medical malpractice.
Net (expense) revenue associated with materials and supplies expense.
Revenue for activities concerned with buying or constructing buildings.
Information about Interfund Loans Receivable.

Program revenues used for Public Safety Services, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base. A department of public safety is a state or local government agency which often has a broad portfolio of responsibilities, which may include some or all of the following: fire services, rescue services, haz-mat services, ambulance and emergency medical services, policing services, emergency communications, inspections and code enforcement, animal control, department of motor vehicle.
Allowance for grants and contracts receivable.

Represent lease contracts payable in more than one year that convey control of the right to use another entity's nonfinancial asset (the underlying asset) as specified in the contract for a period of time in exchange or exchange-like transaction.
Expenses for the acquisition of existing buildings or the contracted building of new buildings.
Unamortized discounts on investments.
Other deferred inflows of resources.
Other salaries. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue earned from tuition and fees assessed against students for educational and general purposes.
Expenses associated with equipment and equipment rental.
Revenue earned from fines and forfeitures and penalties are obtained through penalties and other law enforcement or court activities.
Expenses incurred for refunds and rebates.
Program revenues used for medical care facilities, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Net (expense) revenue associated with salaries and benefits.
Program revenues used for transportation services, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Information about revenues from community and economic development.
Current amount due to the local unit on Interfund loans that have been made in accordance with statutory provisions. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Projects costs, not including capital outlay.
Amounts set aside to pay for debt service for property taxes receivable.
Program revenues used for Public Utilities, including gas, water and electric, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Allowance for land contracts receivable.
Net (expense) revenue from charges for services, parking facilities including garages and meters.
Net (expense) revenue court from miscellaneous court costs and fees.
Revenue earned from investment income and rentals.
Net (Expense) Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for General Pre‐School Education.
Net (expense) revenue associated with housing and community development services when the reporting entity does not separately disclose in the same statement or note.
Information about net (expenses) revenues for instruction.

Program revenues used for community development, which are incremental revenues derived from the specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base. Community development is the practice of taking on activities that provide basic services to communities. It supports the development of strong communities to improve quality of life.

Program revenues used for Public Schools Services, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base. The government interacts with its own schools (known as public schools) at the federal, state, and local level. Each level of government provides a different amount of funding to schools and requires varying degrees of accountability within the schools and school districts.
Revenue for parks and recreation. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Payments made by the State to PERA on behalf of school districts, BOCES and charter schools. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
The amount of amortization expense recognized in the current period for debt issuance.
Allowance for leases receivable.
Revenues earned from the Abstract Department, used on the General Fund. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Net (expense) revenue for land surveying activities performed by a surveyor to perpetuate a previously monumented original public land survey corner, protracted public land survey corner, or property controlling corner.
Financial inflows from other funds of the government reporting entity not classified as interfund services provided, reimbursements or loans.
Other fees earned for transporting individuals to and from activities not classifiable elsewhere.
Amounts collected for or otherwise due to individuals who are wards of the court.
Nonoperating revenues or expenses. Must be used with a typed dimension to indicate a fact which is custom created for that reporting entity.
Revenue from commercial facilities tax.

Revenue for moneys Set‐Aside for specific purposes and identifies those portions of the fund balance (the excess of revenues over expenditures) which are segregated for future purposes and/or are not available to finance expenditures of the subsequent accounting period. Some reserves are statutorily mandated while others are in compliance with generally accepted accounting principles or practices.

Net (Expense) Revenue for activities concerned with paying, transporting, exchanging and maintaining goods and services for the school district. Included are the fiscal and internal services necessary for operating the school district. Include the Chief Business Official and the activities of the Chief Business Official here.
Allowance for deposits receivable.
Costs incurred for professional and contractual services to support the local government unit's operation.

Program revenues that arise from charges to customers, applicants, or others who purchase, use, or directly benefit from the goods, services, or privileges provided, or are otherwise directly affected by the services.

Activity between funds of the primary government, including blended component units. Interfund activities are divided into two broad categories: reciprocal and nonreciprocal. Reciprocal interfund activity comprises interfund loans and interfund services provided and used. Nonreciprocal interfund activity comprises interfund transfers and interfund reimbursements.
Program revenues associated with the station, buildings and equipment maintenance which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Information about revenues from recreation and culture.
Program revenues used for water and sewer systems, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Revenue earned from services rendered, not elsewhere classified.
Program revenues used for golf, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.

Amount due on any legal note that has been accepted by the local unit. It represents an unconditional written promise, signed by the maker, to pay a certain sum on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time either to the bearer or to the order of a person designated therein.
Amount of contributions classified as other. Must be used with a typed dimension to indicate a fact which is custom created for that reporting entity.
Information about Accounts Payable and Accrued Liabilities.
Amounts from due from the State not yet collected. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Parking services.

Expenditures for roads, streets and bridges, used on the General Fund. It reflects all expenditures pertaining to the construction or maintenance of roads, streets or bridges not included under 1951 PA 51. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue from property transfer tax. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Prepaid expenses and other assets. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Capital assets being depreciated, costs before reducing for accumulated depreciation.
Cost of issue of bonds and securities. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Represents amounts owed to the local unit by users of utility services. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Health and welfare.
Name of other cash flows from investing activities which the reporting entity separately discloses in the same statement. Used with the disaggregation line item axis.

Expenditures for training, used on the General Fund or Police (Sheriff) Fund of local units of governments. It reflects such expenditures as the salary of the training officer, police academy expenditures, attendance at training seminars, and other supplies, and expenditures essential to the training program for police officers.

Expenditures for Abstract Department, used on the General Fund. It reflects such expenditures as salaries, travel, supplies, equipment, etc., necessary to operate the abstract office. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Information about personnel statistics.

Amounts due to others that the reporting entity does not separately disclose in the same statement or note. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue earned from grants and entitlement programs not restricted for specific programs.
Public works, infrastructure.
Capital assets at historical cost which is the aggregate of capital assets being depreciated, gross, and capital assets, not being depreciated.
Revenue earned from convention tax levied for convention and trade center services which the consumer pays for lodging on stays less than 30 days at lodging businesses.
Number of police personnel.

Represents lease contracts payable in the current period that convey control of the right to use another entity's nonfinancial asset (the underlying asset) as specified in the contract for a period of time in exchange or exchange-like transaction. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Expenditures for rubbish collection and disposal, used on the General Fund, or in a separate Rubbish Collection Fund. It reflects such expenses as salaries and wages, supplies, materials, maintenance costs, equipment, and all other expenses necessary to render this service. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amounts held by the entity for others to be returned in future periods. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue from business license tax. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Community and economic development services.
Information about investments.

Advances to other funds within the local unit where such advances are due within a year. Examples are advances to a County Drain Revolving Fund for preliminary expenses, advances to a County 100% Tax Payment Fund, advances to an internal service fund, etc. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Revenue earned from corporate tax which is a tax on the profits of a corporation. The taxes are paid on a company's taxable income, which includes revenue minus cost of goods sold (COGS), general and administrative (G&A) expenses, selling and marketing, research and development, depreciation, and other operating costs.
Information about capital assets being depreciated, net of accumulated depreciation and amortization.
Public works, road commission, street department.

Expenditures for animal shelter and dog warden is on the General Fund and reflects such expenditures as salaries, travel expenditures, office supplies, dog tags and supplies, dog food, animal shelter maintenance and other supplies, equipment, and expenditures necessary for the operation of the animal shelter. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Additions to capital assets that are not being depreciated and not being amortized.
Name of other cash flows from non capital financing activities which the reporting entity separately discloses in the same statement. Used with the disaggregation line item axis.

Expenditures for parks supervision, used on the General Fund or on a Park/Recreation Fund. It reflects such expenses as salaries and wages, supplies, materials, and equipment necessary to supervise park operation or recreation programs of a local unit. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Respond to the question, Do all investments comply with P.A. 20 of 1943. For a response of Yes, respond TRUE; response of No, respond FALSE.
Information about state grants to be used for public safety activities.
Capital assets, classified as depreciable, net of accumulated depreciation and amortization.
Sum of all long term liabilities. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Culture and recreation.
Grants, contributions and donations earned from other sources which can include nonprofit organizations and for-profit businesses that provide grants or other types of funding assistance.
Fees paid to fiscal agents. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Used to collect information found on a Capital Assets footnote.
Information about other information on the F65.

Advances to other units of government where such advances are due within a year. An example is an advance to a building authority. Sub-accounts must be used where several units are involved. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue earned from usage of utilities tax which is levied in proportion to gross receipts on public or privately owned public utilities that provide electric, gas, water and/or telephone service.
Public works, sanitation, landfill and solid waste.
Contributions from local government units for general government.
Respond to the question, Are there non-pension funds invested in derivatives at fiscal year-end? For a response of Yes, respond TRUE; response of No, respond FALSE.
Amount of advances to component units where such advances are due within a year. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Transportation services.
Information about Net Position on the Statement of Activities.
Information about expenditures for public works, Road Commission, Non Act 51.

Expenditures for prosecuting attorney, used on the General Fund of county government. Its use is mandatory based on the revised statues of 1846 MCL 49.153 to MCL 49.160. It reflects such expenditures as salaries, travel, supplies, consultants, equipment, etc., necessary for this officer to perform his/her statutory duties as prosecuting attorney for the county. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Reductions from unlimited tax bonds.
An expense that is recognized on the books before it has been paid, categorized as noncurrent. The expense is recorded in the accounting period in which it is incurred.
Revenue earned from investment income and rentals, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Contributions from local government units for gas, water and electric utilities. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amount of redeemable bonds payable during the current fiscal year. Also called demand bonds.
Expenses for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Social Sciences.
Property tax revenue, including delinquent taxes, penalties, interest, fees, and community wide special assessments. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amount of payments related to construction contracts that are due and payable within the normal operating cycle.
Amounts for ambulance services receivable, net of allowance for uncollectible accounts. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue earned from current personal property tax levied.
Net (expense) revenue for fire fighting.
Expenditures for fire prevention. Used on the General Fund or Fire Fund of local units of government that have such an activity reported on a modified accrual basis.
Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Social Sciences.

Compensated absences payable, classified as noncurrent. Compensated absences are compensated time off such as vacation and sick leave, which has been earned by employees and probable that the employer will compensate the employees through paid time off or some other means, such as cash payments at termination or retirement but not yet compensated by the employer.
Amounts for fire protection services accounts receivable, net of allowance for uncollectible accounts. Reported on a modified accrual basis.

Amounts owed by a local unit of government to another local unit where such amounts are due in years subsequent to the current fiscal year. Debit for any subsequent decreases (repayments) of the advance amounts; credit for amounts of advances received and for any subsequent increases.
Reductions from long term debt excluding compensated absences, which are present obligations to sacrifice resources that the government has little or no discretion to avoid.

Expenditures for sewage disposal used on the General Fund, or in a Sewer Fund. It reflects such expenses as salaries and wages, supplies, materials, maintenance costs, equipment, and all other expenses applicable to the operation of a sewage disposal system. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Used in the General Fund of cities and townships and in some villages. Its use is mandatory for units having such a department or officer as well as those units who contract this activity to another entity. It reflects such expenditures as salary, travel, supplies, etc., necessary to perform the required duties. The Equalization Activity Number is found in the General Fund of county government. Its use is mandatory. It reflects such expenses as salaries, travel, supplies, equalization studies, equipment, etc., necessary to perform the function of property tax equalization within the county. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Net (expense) revenue for fire prevention.
Information about the document and the reporting entity.

Non-current portion of accrued known and estimated losses incurred as of the balance sheet date for which no insurance coverage exists, and for which a claim has been made or is probable of being asserted, typically arising from workmen's compensation-type of incidents and personal injury to nonemployees from accidents on the entity's property.
Amounts for emergency medical services receivable, net of allowance for uncollectible accounts. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Information about fines, forfeitures, and penalties.
Net (Expense) Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Social Sciences.
Information about interest paid transit system debt.
Name of the primary government reporting entity.
Net (expense) revenue for training.
Information about expenditures on sanitation landfill, solid waste.
Changes in net position which is the difference in net position between the beginning and end of the reporting period.
Expenditures for general government services. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Expenditures for parks and recreation activities. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Expenditures for other general government services and the reporting entity does not separately disclose in the same statement or note. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Current amount due to the local unit on Interfund loans that have been made in accordance with statutory provisions, net of uncollectible amounts. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Unit identification number issued by the state regulator or authority.
Net (expense) revenue for emergency services.

Other receivables which the reporting entity does not separately disclose in the same statement or note. It is the total due to the entity within one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) from outside sources, including trade accounts receivable, notes and loans receivable, as well as any other types of receivables, net of allowances established for the purpose of reducing such receivables to an amount that approximates net realizable value.

Expenditures for traffic and safety program, used on the General Fund or Police (Sheriff) Fund of local units of governments. It reflects salaries and wages of road patrol personnel, safety program supplies and materials, and other supplies and materials essential to the traffic and safety program.
Funding to component units.

Expenditures for contagious diseases, used on the General Fund of a county. It reflects all expenditures chargeable to public funds for the treatment of contagious diseases, such as tuberculosis, venereal diseases, etc. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amount of bonds maturing in more than one year, and that are payable from restricted assets.

Expenditures for the Sanitation Department, used on the General Fund, or in a separate Rubbish Collection Fund. It reflects such expenses as salaries, travel, office supplies, equipment, and other expenses applicable to the operation of a sanitation department. It may also be used to reflect revenues generated by the sanitation department. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Expenditures for other recreation and culture activities not including parks and recreation, library and various cultural activities, fine arts, historical society, museums, etc. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amounts due from Treasurer.
Unique Entity Identifier (UEI) is the identifier used by entities doing business with the federal government.
Amount of interest paid on all other debt.
Net (expense) revenue for dispatch.
Expenditures for fire stations and buildings other than the general municupal buildings, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Amount of taxes or other amounts collected for or owed to an intermediate school district.
Amount of payments related to contracts that are due and payable in future reporting periods.
Revenue from trailer tax.

Expenditures on drains, public benefit, used on the General Fund. It reflects such expenditures as drain-at-large expenditures paid to the county from the unit’s General Fund and any other public drain expenditure chargeable against all taxpayers of a local unit. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Program revenues used for fire marshal, which are incremental revenues derived from that specific program, generated from sources other than the tax base.
Expenses to fund charter schools.
Type of government which can be reported as State, County, City, Town, Village, Borough, Other general purpose government, School district or Special district.
An acquisition of net assets related to taxes levied that applies to a future reporting period(s).
Expenditures for conservation services. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Expenditures for conservation services.

Represent lease contracts payable in more than one year that convey control of the right to use another entity's nonfinancial asset (the underlying asset) as specified in the contract for a period of time in exchange or exchange-like transaction. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
The portion of interest receivable on special assessments estimated not to be collectible.

Expenses for outlays of governmental funds are not properly classified as expenditures, but still require budgetary or accounting control. These are classified as Other Uses. These include debt service payments (principal and interest) and certain transfers of moneys from one fund to another.
Amounts due from schools. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Expenses for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Music.
Revenue for activities concerned with making nonpermanent improvements or enhancements to building sites. These improvements include fencing, walkways, tunnels and temporary landscaping.

Amount of drain orders payable during the current fiscal year. Drain orders payable in a subsequent year or years are recorded as a deferred inflow. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Information about accrued wages and related liabilities.
Information about expenditures for school district, non instructional services.
Increase (decrease) in deferred outflows, pension items.
Cash paid for interest payment on delinquent taxes purchased.
Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Music.
Number of credit hours earned by students in an academic year.
Changes in total OPEB liabilities attributed to changes in benefit terms.
The portion of interest and penalties receivable estimated not to be collectible.

Expenditures for activities concerned with providing food to students and staff in a school or school district. This service area includes preparing and serving regular and incidental meals, lunches or snacks in connection with school activities and food delivery Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Information about compensated absences payable.
OPEB plan Administrative Expenses.
Information about expenditures for school district, support service programs.
Other cash flows from non capital financing activities, not elsewhere classified. Must be used with a typed dimension to indicate a fact which is custom created for that reporting entity.
Increase (decrease) in deferred outflows, OPEB items.
Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Natural Science.
Amounts owed by a local unit to the federal government due in more than one year. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
The portion of tax liens receivable estimated not to be collectible.
Net (Expense) Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Music.

Capital and related financing activities include (a) acquiring and disposing of capital assets used in providing services or producing goods, (b) borrowing money for acquiring, constructing, or improving capital assets and repaying the amounts borrowed, including interest, and (c) paying for capital assets obtained from vendors on credit.
Amounts due to the primary government within the same reporting entity. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Increase (decrease) in other deferred outflows.
The portion of special assessments liens receivable estimated not to be collectible. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements.
Cash received from property tax payments.
Used to collect financial information about government pension or OPEB plans.
Information about amounts due to other funds.
Changes in total OPEB liabilities attributed to the differences between actual and expected experience.
Increase (decrease) in deferred outflows.
Profit earned from arbitrage that must be paid back (or rebated) to the federal government, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Net (Expense) Revenue for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for Kindergarten through Eighth Grade, K‐8.

Amounts due from townships for most purposes, except for county road commissions or township road agreements. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Expenditures for activities designed to assess and improve the well‐being of students and to supplement the teaching process. These services pertain to interaction between students and teachers by designing the educational program for the needs of individual students. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Expenses for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for elementary, middle or high school for instruction in Natural Science.
The net liability (or asset) of an OPEB plan.
The portion of sales tax receivable estimated not to be collectible. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements.

Amounts collected for and owed to the fiduciary funds within the same reporting entity. Debit for all payments to the fiduciary fund; credit for all amounts owed to the fiduciary fund. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Expenditures for activities dealing directly with the interactions between staff and students for General Elementary Education. Reported on a modified accrual basis.
Increase (decrease) in accounts payable.
Information about noncurrent liabilities.
The portion of income tax receivable estimated not to be collectible. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements.

Net (Expense) Revenue for activities associated with assisting the instructional staff with the content and process of providing learning experiences for students. These services pertain to the interaction between students and teachers, focusing on designing the curriculum training staff on training methods, assessing the student’s learning and retention of the subject matter and delivering and coordinating such activities.

The amount of cash in the form of a separate bank account used only for making payments for personnel services and payroll deductions. Usually, a fixed sum is deposited to this bank account in an amount sufficient to meet the requirements of the bank for carrying the account without service charges, and the local unit for making payments for personnel services between regular pay periods. The principal use of this account is for the deposit of the amount of the gross payroll, against which individual payroll checks and/or direct deposits and payroll deduction checks and/or direct deposits will be drawn. Individual payroll checks and/or direct deposits drawn on this account between regular payroll periods will be included on the next regular payroll voucher. By this method, the fixed sum deposited in the payroll bank account will be replenished each pay period. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
OPEB plan, fiduciary net position, period increase (decrease).
Increase (decrease) in net pension and OPEB liability.
Other cash flows from non capital financing activities, not elsewhere classified.
Reflects the portion of fund balance that is not in spendable form for inventory.
Information about Current Assets.
An acquisition of net assets related to taxes levied that applies to a future reporting period(s). Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Allowance for the portion of delinquent taxes estimated to be uncollectible.
Other financing options, noncurrent, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Increase (decrease) in accrued salaries and benefits.
Cash received from tax levied.
Estimated amounts due to third party payers in more than one year which are entities other than the patient or healthcare provider that reimburses and manages health care expenses.

Expenditures for health and welfare, community action project used on the General Fund of a special Federal Project Fund. It includes such expenditures as salaries and wages of local unit personnel involved, advertising expenditures, appropriations or contractual payments to local agencies assisting in such programs, supplies, materials, and other expenditures essential to programs aimed at stimulating economic opportunity within the unit. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Expenses incurred within the General Fund or a Sewer Fund of a local unit of government. Its use is mandatory for units having a sewage disposal system. It reflects such expenses as salaries and wages, supplies, materials, maintenance costs, equipment, and all other expenses applicable to the operation of a sewage disposal system.
State grants for culture and recreation purposes. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.

Represents the amount due on any legal note that has been accepted by the local unit, net allowance for uncollectible amounts, due within one year. It represents an unconditional written promise, signed by the maker, to pay a certain sum on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time either to the bearer or to the order of a person designated therein. Used for amounts on the governmental funds statements, reported on a modified accrual basis.
Waterworks system.

State grants for land surveying activities performed by a surveyor to perpetuate a previously monumented original public land survey corner, protracted public land survey corner, or property controlling corner.
